{
  "text": "Preventive Medicine Reports j o u r n a l h o m e p a g e : h t t p : / / e e s . e l s e v i e r . c o m / p m e d r upgrades to corner stores. As interventions in small stores proliferate, early results, some assessed by validated, comprehensive store audits [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] and some assessed by study-specific measurement tools, [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] demonstrate good success at increasing the availability of healthy foods [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] [CITATION_10] . Only a few evaluations, however, have compared corner stores involved in healthy initiatives to stores that are not [CITATION_11] [CITATION_12] .",
